The paper deals with complexity and approximation results for a combinatorial optimization problem, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of regret minimization and scenario uncertainty representation suggests that it could be in the sub-category of cs.GT (Game Theory), while the use of approximation algorithms suggests it could be in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The problem formulation and the use of algorithms also suggest it could be in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
